The function to find sequences of lowercase letters joined with an underscore using regex is provided as follows:

import re

def text_match(text):
    pattern = r'([a-z]+)_([a-z]+)
    matches = re.findall(pattern, text)
    if len(matches) > 0:
        return 'Found a match!' 
    else:
        return 'Not matched!'
